qas.question: What text is written and sent to the Senate if the House approves of a law?

answers.text: "The Second Chamber of the States General sends the following approved proposal of law to the First Chamber"

qas.question: What text is written and sent back to the government if a bill is rejected?

answers.text: The Second Chamber of the States General has rejected the accompanying proposal of law."

qas.question: If the Senate approves the law after receiving it from the House, what is written and sent to the government?

answers.text: "To the King, The States General have accepted the proposal of law as it is offered here."

qas.question: What is one thing that could happen after the House of Lords debates the law?

plausible_answers.text: it sends it back to the government

qas.question: If the lower house approves the law, what happens?

plausible_answers.text: "The Second Chamber of the States General sends the following approved proposal of law to the First Chamber"

qas.question: What text is sent to the House of Representatives if a law is approved?

plausible_answers.text: "The Second Chamber of the States General has rejected the accompanying proposal of law."

qas.question: What text is sent to the House of Representatives if a law is not approved?

context: After the House of Representatives has debated the law, it either <b3_0>approves it<b3_0/> and sends it to the Senate with the text <a0_0><b5_0>"The Second Chamber of the States General sends the following approved proposal of law to the First Chamber"<b5_0/><a0_0/>, or it rejects it and returns it to the government with the text <b6_0>"<a1_0>The Second Chamber of the States General has rejected the accompanying proposal of law."<b6_0/><a1_0/> If the upper house then approves the law, <b4_0>it sends it back to the government<b4_0/> with the text <a2_0>"To the King, The States General have accepted the proposal of law as it is offered here."
